You are given a string s. You can convert s to a palindrome by adding characters in front of it.
Return the shortest palindrome you can find by performing this transformation.

Example 1:

Input: s = "aacecaaa"
Output: "aaacecaaa"
Example 2:

Input: s = "abcd"
Output: "dcbabcd"


class Solution {
    public String shortestPalindrome(String s) {
        String rev = new StringBuilder(s).reverse().toString();
        String combined = s + "#" + rev;
        int[] lps = new int[combined.length()];
        for (int i = 1; i < combined.length(); i++)
        {
            int j = lps[i - 1];
            while (j > 0 && combined.charAt(i) != combined.charAt(j)) 
                j = lps[j - 1];
            if (combined.charAt(i) == combined.charAt(j)) 
                j++;
            lps[i] = j;
        }
        int longestPrefix = lps[combined.length() - 1];
        return rev.substring(0, s.length() - longestPrefix) + s;
    }
}


Time Complexity: O(n)
- Building reverse string: O(n)
- Constructing combined string: O(n)
- Computing KMP prefix table: O(n)
- Final string construction: O(n)
Overall: O(n)

Space Complexity: O(n)
- Reverse string: O(n)
- Combined string: O(n)
- LPS array: O(n)
Overall: O(n)


